cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.AI

The paper proposes a novel neural network architecture for 3D object reconstruction from images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the limitations of traditional SFM/SLAM methods, which are related to robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses synthetic data for training, which is related to computer graphics (cs.GR).
